 Port Elizabeth - The Eastern Cape Provincial Organised Crime Investigation Unit (Gang Investigation) arrested a 26-year-old suspect about two hours after an alleged murder took place in Willam Slammert Drive in Bloemendal, Port Elizabeth, on Monday morning. "It is alleged that on Monday, at about 04:45, Juandre Mentoor (29) and a friend were walking in Willam Slammert Drive in Bloemendal, Bethelsdorp, when they saw the suspect running towards them," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "The suspect then started shooting at them. Mentoor and his friend (23) started running. "Mentoor collapsed a short distance in William Slammert Drive and died. "He sustained multiple gunshot wounds to his upper body." She said that his gang affiliation is not known at this stage. "Investigations in the immediate vicinity led the investigators to a house in Willam Slammert Drive where the suspect was found sleeping." Col Naidu said that the incident is gang-related and the suspect is detained on a charge of murder. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 